ashendb.helper module#

async ashendb.helper.match_data(data: Document, query: dict) → bool#

Match a document with a query.

Parameters:

  • data (Document) – The document to match.

  • query (dict) – The query to match with.

Return type:

bool

Example

>>> await match_data({"name": "Ashen"}, {"name": "Ashen"})
True

Note

All the operators might not work. Please report as bug.

async ashendb.helper.update_data(document: Document, update: dict) → Document#

Update a document with the given update query.

Parameters:

  • document (Document) – The document to update.

  • update (dict) – The update query.

Return type:

Document

Example

>>> document = {"name": "John", "age": 20}
>>> update = {"$set": {"age": 21}}
>>> await update_data(document, update)
{"name": "John", "age": 21}

Note

All the operators might not work. Please report as bug.
